-- Persian Gulf Stocks: Ithmaar Bank of Bahrain, Tabreed of U.A.E.
-- B y   A l a a   S h a h i n e   a n d   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 2012-05-17T10:40:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-17/persian-gulf-stocks-ithmaar-bank-of-bahrain-tabreed-of-u-a-e-.html
Dubai’s benchmark  DFM General Index (DFMGI) 
gained the most since April 24, advancing 0.7 percent to
1,475.58 at the 2 p.m. close in the emirate. The measure
declined 2.6 percent this week. Bahrain’s BB All Share Index
fell 0.4 percent.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Ithmaar Bank BSC (ITHMR)   plunged 14 percent, the most
since Bloomberg started tracking the shares in 2006, to 19 cents
after the Bahrain-based investment bank was removed from the
MSCI Small Cap Indices, according to a document obtained by
Bloomberg News.  National Central Cooling Co. (TABREED)   rose 3.4 percent,
the most since May 7, to 1.23 dirhams. The United Arab Emirates’
utility known as Tabreed said it completed the expansion of its
district cooling plant in Al Ain.  To contact the reporters on this story:
